* Okorocha takes oath as senator By Deji Elumoye in Abuja The Senate on Thursday went into a close-door session to address some salient ‘house keeping’ issues. This was announced at the resumption of plenary by Senate President Ahmad Lawan at 11.07am after a motion to that effect had been moved by Deputy Senate President Ovie Omo-Agege. Earlier, the former governor of Imo State, Rochas Okorocha, was sworn in as a senator of the Federal Republic. Okorocha, representing Imo West, was administered the oath of office by the Clerk of the Senate, Mr Nelson Ayewoh. Details later…